comments: Brunson (DAL) engages and disengages with Bogdanovic (UTA) as Bogdanovic moves to set the pick.

Dinwiddie (DAL) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Bogdanovic's (UTA) right wrist after the release. Dinwiddie is jumping to the side of Bogdanovic and would avoid Bogdanovic's right foot if he didn't extend it out to the side to initiate the marginal contact thereafter.
O'Neale (UTA) is moving alongside Doncic's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs with Doncic's side as they move over the pick.
Mitchell (UTA) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Finney-Smith's (DAL) upper body after the release.
O'Neale (UTA) turns slightly as he braces for the impending contact with Brunson (DAL), which O'Neale absorbs as he sets the pick.

O'Neale (UTA) jumps forward in pursuit of the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Brunson's (DAL) face prior to O'Neale making contact with the ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
O'Neale (UTA) and Bullock (DAL) engage and disengage with one another as the pick is set.

O'Neale (UTA) initiates contact with Brunson's (DAL) right foot and left side, affecting Brunson's SQBR at the end of the drive.  O'Neale leans in and head to head contact occurs with Brunson.  Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bullock (DAL) places his arm on Conley's (UTA) back and as he stops short and changes directions, Conley's momentum carries him forward.
O'Neale (UTA) briefly has his arms around Finney-Smith's (DAL) upper half before correcting.
Bullock (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Gobert's (UTA) path and gives Gobert a step of distance to avoid the contact, which Bullock absorbs.
Finney-Smith (DAL) makes clean contact with the ball and partially dislodges it away from Mitchell (UTA) prior to any incidental arm contact occurring.
After the ball is partially dislodged away, Mitchell (UTA) re-gains full control of the ball while airborne and his right foot legally returns to the floor prior to the release of the pass.
Doncic (DAL) brushes Gobert's (UTA) right arm and marginal contact occurs prior to the start of Gobert's upward shooting motion.
Finney-Smith (DAL) avoids making contact with Gobert's (UTA) right elbow and legally contests the layup attempt.
O'Neale (UTA) brings his right hand forward and marginal contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) left forearm near halfcourt.
Finney-Smith (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in O'Neale's (UTA) path and absorbs the contact as the defensive switch takes place.
Gobert (UTA) maintains a rested forearm on Doncic's (DAL) side after Doncic's gather and marginal contact occurs as Doncic fades away from the basket during the driving shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (DAL) rests his hand on Conley's (UTA) back before he makes the pass and the contact is marginal.
Conley (UTA) gathers on his left foot and steps with his right foot to establish a pivot. In an effort to evade defenders, he drags his pivot foot forward before releasing the pass.
Bogdanovic (UTA) commits a take foul on Brunson (DAL).
Clarkson (UTA) and Dinwiddie (DAL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
